WOULD-BE-ROBBERS were stopped in their tracks after they were bust before they could go ahead with their mission. This is after the Northern Cape Organised Crime Detectives assisted by Kimberley Flying Squad, Kimberley K9 Unit and Warrenton Visible police members, foiled a possible armed robbery and arrested the six suspects. Police Captain Olebogeng Tawana said in a statement, "The suspects were on a mission to execute an armed robbery in Holpan near Windsorton. "On Saturday, 09 July 2022, the team operationalised intelligence regarding an armed robbery which was planned to be executed in Holpan. The suspects' vehicle was intercepted on the Holpan gravel road and searched. The suspects were found in possession of four unlicensed firearms." READ: Couple sent to jail for robbery Tawana said the suspects are expected to appear in the Barkley West Magistrate’s Court on Monday, 11 July 2022 on counts of conspiracy to commit a robbery and possession of unlicensed firearms and ammunition. The Northern Cape Acting Deputy Provincial Commissioner for Crime Detection, Brigadier Nicky Mills commended the team for acting promptly to bring the perpetrators to book. And also indicated that the proliferation of firearms will be vigorously enforced in the province.  